-- Chinese Industries Attacked by Cyber Virus, Morning Post Reports
-- B y   S t a n l e y   J a m e s
-- 2010-09-29T22:53:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-29/chinese-industries-attacked-by-cyber-virus-morning-post-reports.html
China’s key industries have been
hit by a computer virus know as Stuxnet that attacks Siemens AG
systems, the South China Morning Post reported, citing Xinhua
news agency.  The virus has infected six million computers in China and
“nearly a thousand” industries, the report said, citing
Xinhua. The source for the attack is in the US, according to the
report.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stanley James at 
 sjames8@bloomberg.net  